choices.text:
___ . I don’t answer that there were no soccer fields like the ones they played in. Her first response is, “Where I’m from, there are lots of soccer fields because people play soccer, but there’s no war, and there’s peace and there’s happiness and people share and help each other.” Little does she know, she’s correct on all accounts.

She continues, “I am a young boy. Wow, is that your face? You are very purty.” I still married that little boy. Married, polygamous babies, they finish each other’s sentences like back in the ’90’s Buffy’s.

“Yes, I am the princess and I don’t want to marry him,” she protests. Then she says, “I’m a princess!!!”

Haaaaahahahahaha

And she was. Remember the best story ever from the trip? The story of the princess?? Marataba slayed Lord Greyskull, defeated 20 evil men on his way to Zuleka’s castle where he saved her from a fire-breathing dragon, that, unbeknownst to the princess, was her brother’s cat. She is a princess, no fairy tale needed. This kid is going places, you all need to watch out for Marataba. Pack your bags, Australia is calling, because Australia is pumped, excited, and girl crazy about Marataba.
